Japan Server 
Akihabara 
City/ No Monsters 
No PVP
Entry Restrictions/ None 
Exit Restrictions/ None</b>

19:18.300 --> 19:22.800
<b>Silver Plaza
Japan Server 
Merchant's Hall/ Silver Plaza 
City/ No Monsters 
No PVP
Entry Restrictions/ None 
Exit Restrictions/ None</b>

19:19.900 --> 19:21.490
Oh, Akatsuki...

19:21.490 --> 19:23.560
You look great. So cute!

19:23.560 --> 19:25.590
Oh, I can't... I can't even...

19:23.920 --> 19:26.350
You didn't say anything about 
being in a fashion show!

19:26.350 --> 19:28.310
Didn't you say I'd be working in the background?

19:28.510 --> 19:30.380
That's right...

19:30.380 --> 19:32.190
The clothing is the star of the show.

19:32.740 --> 19:34.190
I didn't lie to you.

19:35.130 --> 19:37.190
You wear this, Shiro!

19:37.530 --> 19:38.990
This?

19:38.990 --> 19:41.110
I think it'll look good, my lord.

19:41.110 --> 19:42.530
But I'm not laughing.

19:43.030 --> 19:46.650
I haven't seen this many people 
in a long time, though...

19:47.040 --> 19:49.630
I told you I'd pay!

19:49.890 --> 19:52.080
Th-The money isn't the issue!

19:53.980 --> 19:54.820
What?

19:55.180 --> 19:56.090
Minori?

19:56.960 --> 19:58.270
Is something wrong?

19:58.590 --> 20:06.220
<b>Cocoa Brown</b>

19:59.300 --> 20:02.670
I've come all the way from 
the far west to buy this stuff.

20:02.670 --> 20:06.220
But it's only two items per customer...

20:06.220 --> 20:12.600
<b>Nemimi/ Adventurer</b>

20:06.220 --> 20:12.600
<b>Constantan/ Person of the Land</b>

20:06.420 --> 20:10.350
I can make you famous across the land!

20:10.350 --> 20:12.600
That isn't what we want.

20:12.780 --> 20:14.170
What?

20:14.170 --> 20:15.110
Yes, yes.

20:15.550 --> 20:17.650
I understand your point.

20:17.650 --> 20:18.990
But they feel differently.

20:19.420 --> 20:20.760
Please leave.

20:22.010 --> 20:24.200
I've got nothing to say to a young kid like you!

20:24.200 --> 20:25.410
Move!

20:28.150 --> 20:31.480
You will leave, won't you?

20:33.660 --> 20:34.900
Now I'm mad.

20:34.900 --> 20:36.630
I'm never coming back.

20:37.040 --> 20:38.960
Thank you...

20:38.960 --> 20:43.040
If he'd bought everything, I wouldn't have 
the fun of selling them one a time.

20:43.660 --> 20:45.020
You're welcome.

20:46.640 --> 20:47.390
<i>That's strange.</i>

20:48.400 --> 20:50.470
<i>Why would he leave so easily?</i>

20:51.200 --> 20:53.400
Hey, how long do I have to wait?

20:53.400 --> 20:55.060
I'm here to do business, you know!

20:55.060 --> 20:57.200
I'm asking you how many you have!

20:57.200 --> 20:58.430
We really can't do that...

20:58.430 --> 21:00.600
I'm not moving until you say yes.

20:59.630 --> 21:01.180
Please stop...

21:00.600 --> 21:02.530
How much do I have to pay for a whole box?

21:03.060 --> 21:04.580
What's wrong, my lord?

21:04.920 --> 21:07.030
The place is getting rowdy.

21:07.230 --> 21:09.580
Yes, more than I'd anticipated.

21:10.110 --> 21:12.040
The People of the Land are acting strangely.

21:13.030 --> 21:14.600
But I don't understand it.

21:15.110 --> 21:16.530
I can't get a clear enough picture.

21:18.000 --> 21:20.170
I feel like I'm missing something...

21:22.650 --> 21:24.050
It's me, Minori.

21:24.490 --> 21:26.660
I'm going through the paperwork,

21:26.660 --> 21:27.850
and something isn't right.

21:28.280 --> 21:32.180
Some of the paperwork overlaps, 
and some of their math is wrong.

21:32.520 --> 21:35.280
There's a huge number of very basic errors.

21:35.280 --> 21:36.190
And...

21:36.520 --> 21:39.940
Most of them come from People of the Land.

21:40.580 --> 21:41.710
I see...

21:42.130 --> 21:43.450
So that's it.

21:43.660 --> 21:45.860
My lord, what will we do about the show?

21:45.860 --> 21:48.230
Minori, keep this line open.

21:48.230 --> 21:48.950
Right.

21:49.780 --> 21:54.510
Akatsuki, find Isaac and get 
a report on our security.

21:56.460 --> 22:00.760
It looks like someone is attacking Akihabara.

22:01.560 --> 22:02.900
Attacking?

22:02.900 --> 22:04.510
An enemy?

22:05.420 --> 22:07.620
I'm going to my office in the guild building.

22:08.050 --> 22:09.680
This may be an emergency.

22:09.680 --> 22:10.700
Understood.

22:13.030 --> 22:14.120
Shiroe...

22:15.450 --> 22:16.680
<i>I let down my guard!</i>

22:17.080 --> 22:18.610
<i>All the signs were there.</i>

22:19.210 --> 22:20.250
<i>But I was careless...</i>

22:21.520 --> 22:23.560
<i>Now they have the advantage!</i>

22:23.690 --> 22:27.110
<b>New Spirit Ship 

Eagle</b>

22:27.210 --> 22:29.240
We'll be arriving in approximately thirty minutes.

22:30.590 --> 22:33.720
Prepare to disembark, Lord Malves.

24:05.960 --> 24:08.370
The town of Akihabara is under attack.

24:08.370 --> 24:10.890
Shiroe senses the enemy, and takes action.

24:10.890 --> 24:14.860
But his guesswork is off, and his calculations fail.

24:14.860 --> 24:17.140
The Round Table faces grave danger.

24:17.140 --> 24:18.840
What is the enemy really after?

24:18.840 --> 24:22.400
In the hour of greatest peril, the strategist 
Shiroe begins his counterattack.

24:22.400 --> 24:24.210
Next time: Chaos.

24:22.400 --> 24:29.990
<b>Chaos</b>

24:24.780 --> 24:26.920
We will change the world.
